&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;About SHEIN&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;SHEIN is a global online fashion and lifestyle retailer, offering SHEIN branded apparel and products from a global network of vendors, all at affordable prices. Headquartered in Singapore, with more than 15,000 employees operating from offices around the world, SHEIN is committed to making the beauty of fashion accessible to all, promoting its industry-leading, on-demand production methodology, for a smarter, future-ready industry.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Position Summary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;We’re seeking a full-time Associate Buyer for our&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Los Angeles-based &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;corporate office.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;This position offers immense flexibility and excellent long-term growth potential. The ideal candidate will be trained from the ground up on core merchandising and visual workflows. They will own the end-to-end sample lifecycle, assist with product styling and outfit coordination, build photoshoot presentations, and manage new item launch linking systems. This role serves as a dynamic operational backbone, absorbing administrative and logistical workflows to ensure product readiness, data accuracy, and visually compelling launches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. Styling &amp;amp; Photoshoot Support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trend &amp;amp; Styling Alignment: Assist the senior buyer with daily product styling, outfit combinations, and visual coordination, developing a strong eye for trend execution from the ground up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Photoshoot Asset Preparation: Prepare the photoshoot presentation (PPT) at least one week in advance, including finalized product lists and curated outfit pairings for manager review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Studio Coordination: Coordinate with the Creative and Studio teams to schedule and prepare for upcoming photoshoots based on incoming sample arrivals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sample Readiness: Ensure all clothing, shoes, and accessory samples required for photoshoots are organized, labeled, and ready for onset utilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Studio Alignment: Partner with the Creative and Studio teams to ensure the photoshoot schedule runs smoothly without delays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Issue Resolution: Track and communicate any missing or delayed samples to the relevant teams promptly, adjusting shoot schedules as needed to eliminate production downtime.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2. New Item Launch &amp;amp; Linking Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Launch Schedule Oversight: Monitor the weekly new item launching schedule to ensure all SKC targets are met accurately and on time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekly Plan Submissio

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;About SHEIN&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;SHEIN is a global online fashion and lifestyle retailer, offering SHEIN branded apparel and products from a global network of vendors, all at affordable prices. Headquartered in Singapore, with more than 15,000 employees operating from offices around the world, SHEIN is committed to making the beauty of fashion accessible to all, promoting its industry-leading, on-demand production methodology, for a smarter, future-ready industry.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Position Summary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a full-time Buying Manager (official title: Buying Manager I) for our Los Angeles based corporate office. Lead product strategy and brand growth for SHEIN&#39;s premium womenswear sub-brand(s) – Hauture. Within this role, you will be responsible for shaping the brand&#39;s product direction from seasonal assortment planning to development, launch strategy, and performance review. Our ideal candidate brings strong fashion judgment, business acumen, and brand leadership experience, with the ability to turn trend and sales insights into commercially successful product assortments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define brand positioning, seasonal direction, and long-term product strategy in partnership with senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead assortment planning and product development for each launch, balancing trend relevance, brand consistency, and business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage development quotas and launch pacing to improve efficiency, reduce risk, and keep the brand responsive to emerging trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review product selections to ensure alignment with brand identity, quality standards, color strategy, and overall assortment needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze business performance, including CTR, CR, GMV, and category results, and adjust product and launch strategies accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with visual, studio, and merchandising teams to improve content performance and support stronger product storytelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior and mid-level buyers and establish clear processes and standards across the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage supplier relationships and work closely with ODM partners to drive speed, quality, and cost efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor fashion trends, customer demand, and market shifts, especially in the North American womenswear market, to identify growth opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Job Requirements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span

